Did you check our FAQ on the subject?

  Properties glossary
  http://mathforum.org/dr.math/faq/faq.property.glossary.html

You've got the additive inverse right, but the multiplicative inverse 
of a number is the number by which you multiply it to get 1 (which is 
the multiplicative identity).

If you have any further questions, feel free to write back.


